GIT (port-9418)


basic commands

-install git (yum install git -y)
-git status
-git init(to create local repository)
	repository will be created in name master
	to change local repository name(git branch -m <name>)
-to move your file into staging area(git add <name>)
-to move your file from staging area to local repository(git commit -m)
-for second time moving a file from working stage to local repo(git commit -am)
		no need to ad

User configuration:
------------------- 
git config --global user.name "10amsession"
git config --global user.name.email "sasijobsupporet@gmail.com"

for specific user:
------------------
# git config user.name "mani"
# git config user.email "manisa1980@gmail.com"

-git log
-git log --online
-git log (log id) for specific log
							Branch-

master is the main branch
we need to create a copy of the  content(master branch)
and we should work on copy in feature branch


feature branch create( git branch <feature branch name>)
master branch to freature branch(git checkout fb name)

Merge-


smooth and conflict merge

merge command (git merge <name>) 
conflict merge- to resolve conflict we need to use conflict tool

To resolve conflict , we need to use mergetool:
-----------------------------------------------
git config --global merge.tool vimdiff
git config --global merge.conflictstyle diff3
git config --global mergetool.prompt false

git mergetool

Rebase-git rebase master
cherry pick-git cherry-pick logid

git stash-to pull the code from staging area to working dir


